    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Reservations for the Asking</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Nancy Intrator letter, commenting on July 19 article, deplores practice of lying in order to obtain reservations at Manhattan's trendy and expensive restaurants (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I, for one, have had it with all the articles about getting reservations at  ''in'' restaurants (''Had a Reservation. Honest.'' July 19) Who cares?  Years ago in France, I had several good meals at not only Alain Ducasse's restaurant, but many Michelin-starred restaurants, and it took a phone call on the same afternoon to book.</p>
        <p>JOHN HARRINGTON  New York</p>
      </block>
